@base = http://localhost:5251
@key  = dev-key-change-me

### Health (no auth)
GET {{base}}/health

### Create invoice - expected 201
POST {{base}}/invoices
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{key}}

{
  "invoiceId": "INV-1001",
  "customer":  "Acme Corp",
  "amount":    1500.00,
  "dueDate":   "2026-04-01"
}

### Create another (different customer for fuzzy testing)
POST {{base}}/invoices
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{key}}

{
  "invoiceId": "INV-1002",
  "customer":  "Globex Industries",
  "amount":    2750.50,
  "dueDate":   "2026-04-05"
}

### List invoices - expected 200
GET {{base}}/invoices
X-API-Key: {{key}}

### Reference match — should auto-close INV-1001
POST {{base}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{key}}

{
  "paymentId":   "PAY-5001",
  "payerName":   "Acme Corp",
  "amount":      1500.00,
  "reference":   "INV-1001",
  "paymentDate": "2026-04-02"
}

### Fuzzy match — "Globex Ind." vs "Globex Industries", invoice stays OPEN
POST {{base}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{key}}

{
  "paymentId":   "PAY-5002",
  "payerName":   "Globex Ind.",
  "amount":      2750.50,
  "reference":   "Payment for April",
  "paymentDate": "2026-04-06"
}

### Wrong API key — expected 401
GET {{base}}/invoices
X-API-Key: wrong-key

### Bad request — expected 400
POST {{base}}/invoices
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{key}}

### Unmatchable — match field will be null
POST {{base}}/payments
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{key}}

{
  "paymentId":   "PAY-5099",
  "payerName":   "Mystery Payer",
  "amount":      9999.99,
  "reference":   "",
  "paymentDate": "2026-04-30"
}


